{
  "stem": "12053.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were so happy to have found our parents.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my friends used to come and visit them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that's when I felt such a guilt complex.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The friend I was telling you about just now, [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Irma, ?] and another friend who died about two years ago, a very close friend, [?",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Louise ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Bergman-- ?] and in fact, [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Louise ?] told me one thing that bears out the story I told you on the first tape.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She was a German Jewess, very Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And she told me that in my first husband's house, she learned who were Polish Jews.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they weren't perhaps too tidy, and my mother-in-law was hardworking and that.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "She said that's where she learned about hospitality.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They had an open house.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They took in all the refugees for meals, for [INAUDIBLE], for Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "She said, never would I have believed that it would look-- in-- in-- all she heard in Germany was the dirty Polish Juden, the Polish Jews, from her parents and aunts and uncles who were very fine people, but they were-- she said, in Germany, I would have never been allowed to be a best friend to you.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "She admitted it to me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And she said true hospitality she learned from the Polish Jews in Birmingham.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "So this is just to tie it up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And my first husband came-- also from Polish background.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He came to England after the First War with his-- his brothers and his parents.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So they had truly an open house, and they were Polish Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And there we never felt any-- being slighted or anything.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
